      <td width="100%"><font face="Arrus BT">51<font size="3"> I thank <font color="#800080"><strong>Geoffrey S. Smith</strong></font>
      (Department of History, Queen's University), and <font color="#800080"><strong>Charlotte </strong></font><font color="#000000">and</font><font color="#800080"><strong> Ruth Forsdyke</strong></font> for
      most helpful editorial comments. The painting of 207
      William Street by Jane Redpath Drummond (1916) was exhibited at the <font color="#C60000"><em><strong>Agnes
      Etherington Arts Centre</strong></em></font>, and the above photograph (courtesy of <font color="#800080"><strong>Dorothy Farr</strong></font>) is displayed with the permission of <font color="#800080"><strong>Mr. Douglas Petty</strong></font> (owner of the original
      painting).</font></font></td>
